    <h2 class="section-title">What is Swiss Punk?</h2>
    
    <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <strong>Swiss Punk</strong> (also known as New Wave Typography) emerged in the <span style="background-color: #FFFF00; padding: 0 4px;">1970s</span> as a rebellious response to the rigid, minimalist Swiss typography that dominated corporate design.
    </p>
    
    <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      Led by <strong>Wolfgang Weingart</strong> at the Basel School of Design, this movement embraced chaos, intuition, and expression—shattering the "less is more" philosophy with layered compositions, diagonal type, and intentionally broken grids.
    </p>
    
